summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Three Hundred Fifty ($350.00) Dollars out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of Mary S. Noland and James Noland for personal injuries received by said May S. Noland on East Denny Way, between Twenty-fifth and Twenty-sixth Avenues, on the 30th day of April, 1907, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
